subject: Re: incomplete = true
msgSnippet: To shorten, how come the last test shows complete, the stats show all complete but all the individual tests before the last one show incomplete = true. Per
messageBody:
To shorten, how come the last test shows complete, the stats show all
complete but all the individual tests before the last one show
incomplete = true. Per Junit Recipe "Build a data-driven test suite"
from JB Rainsberger's "Junit Recipes" book (Excellent book),

My Suite Method is:

public static Test suite() throws Exception {
TestSuite suite = new TestSuite();
TestSuite namedsuite;
String Item[] = new String[] {"Item 0", "Item 1" .... };
String ItemNames[] = new String[] {"Item 0 Name", "Item 1 .... };

for (int i=0; i<Item.length; i++) {
namedsuite = new TestSuite();
namedsuite.setName("Load " + Item[i] + " - " + ItemNames[i]);
namedsuite.addTest(new ProcessTest(Item[0], ItemNames[0]);
suite.addTest(namedsuite);
}
